1
00:00:05,968 --> 00:00:07,885
EPISODE 58
TOKYO NO. 1 COLONY, PART 5

2
00:00:07,885 --> 00:00:08,885
EPISODE 58
TOKYO NO. 1 COLONY, PART 5

3
00:00:10,845 --> 00:00:12,946
Domain Expansion.

4
00:00:13,156 --> 00:00:14,838
Chimera Shadow Garden.

5
00:00:20,387 --> 00:00:24,044
Esoteric Technique.
Hollow Wicker Basket.

6
00:00:26,271 --> 00:00:29,004
[NARRATOR] Hollow Wicker Basket
is the origin

7
00:00:29,004 --> 00:00:31,779
of New Shadow Style's
"Simple Domain."

8
00:00:31,989 --> 00:00:33,509
It possesses the ability
to neutralize a domain

9
00:00:33,721 --> 00:00:36,451
and counter
its guaranteed-hit factor.

10
00:00:36,451 --> 00:00:38,199
This won't end well for you.

11
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:39,606
-[thuds]
-[gasps]

12
00:00:39,606 --> 00:00:40,758
[NARRATOR]
The "Domain Amplification"

13
00:00:40,758 --> 00:00:43,104
used by Jogo and Hanami
in Shibuya

14
00:00:43,317 --> 00:00:45,450
used a domain
capable of guaranteed-hit,

15
00:00:45,662 --> 00:00:46,814
guaranteed-kill technique.

16
00:00:46,814 --> 00:00:48,136
[groans]

17
00:00:50,353 --> 00:00:52,102
[REGGIE]
How was he able to hit me?

18
00:00:52,486 --> 00:00:54,277
[NARRATOR] But they
intentionally left a space

19
00:00:54,490 --> 00:00:56,025
in their cursed techniques

20
00:00:56,025 --> 00:00:58,925
so that Gojo's cursed technique
could flow into it,

21
00:00:59,139 --> 00:01:01,143
neutralizing his Limitless.

22
00:01:01,356 --> 00:01:04,810
However, Hollow Wicker Basket
and Simple Domain aren't capable

23
00:01:05,024 --> 00:01:06,985
of neutralizing
the cursed technique.

24
00:01:07,199 --> 00:01:09,799
So instead, they work
by neutralizing the barrier

25
00:01:09,799 --> 00:01:11,549
that's imbued
with cursed technique.

26
00:01:11,932 --> 00:01:14,021
In this way,
the imbued technique's

27
00:01:14,021 --> 00:01:16,964
guaranteed-hit effect
is nullified.

28
00:01:16,964 --> 00:01:18,713
[groans]

29
00:01:19,438 --> 00:01:22,807
[NARRATOR] But Fushiguro's
domain is incomplete.

30
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:25,536
Guess that wiped
the sneer off your face.

31
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:26,750
You damn brat!

32
00:01:27,672 --> 00:01:28,930
[spits]

33
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:30,356
[NARRATOR]
When he transposed his domain

34
00:01:30,566 --> 00:01:32,201
onto the space of the gymnasium,

35
00:01:32,412 --> 00:01:34,215
an unexpected consequence
happened.

36
00:01:34,425 --> 00:01:36,564
It forced his domain to close.

37
00:01:36,564 --> 00:01:39,290
It is not imbued
with a guaranteed-hit technique.

38
00:01:39,499 --> 00:01:40,884
[grunts]

39
00:01:41,094 --> 00:01:42,856
You're acting
like you've already won!

40
00:01:43,065 --> 00:01:44,197
[groans]

41
00:01:44,197 --> 00:01:45,875
[REGGIE] Now I get it.

42
00:01:46,085 --> 00:01:47,595
[NARRATOR]
Chimera Shadow Garden.

43
00:01:47,804 --> 00:01:48,937
It is currently extending

44
00:01:48,937 --> 00:01:51,202
Fushiguro's Ten Shadows
Technique,

45
00:01:51,412 --> 00:01:52,670
and as it does so,

46
00:01:52,670 --> 00:01:56,654
draws out 120%
of his latent potential.

47
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,380
Unfortunately for Reggie Star,

48
00:01:59,591 --> 00:02:02,191
that very imperfection
is what caught him off-guard.

49
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:04,162
[REGGIE] Both his clothes
and his shikigami

50
00:02:04,372 --> 00:02:06,763
had physical forms
before striking me.

51
00:02:06,972 --> 00:02:08,357
That means this barrier

52
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:10,873
isn't imbued
with a guaranteed-hit technique.

53
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:13,222
The domain's buff
to his technique's abilities

54
00:02:13,222 --> 00:02:14,648
is no joke, though.

55
00:02:14,857 --> 00:02:16,241
This is even worse to deal with

56
00:02:16,452 --> 00:02:18,381
than a simple
guaranteed-hit domain.

57
00:02:18,591 --> 00:02:20,142
If he pulls
that elephant out here

58
00:02:20,353 --> 00:02:21,611
and drenches me in water,

59
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:24,002
it'll take away
half of my options

60
00:02:24,002 --> 00:02:25,763
and I'll probably lose.

61
00:02:28,489 --> 00:02:29,747
[groans]

62
00:02:31,006 --> 00:02:32,222
[Megumi grunts]

63
00:02:33,648 --> 00:02:35,075
[REGGIE] But, you know,

64
00:02:35,284 --> 00:02:36,710
it's so like me

65
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:39,268
to make sure
that won't happen.

66
00:02:40,820 --> 00:02:42,582
-[MEGUMI] Nue!
-[Nue screeches]

67
00:02:42,791 --> 00:02:43,791
[Reggie grunts]

68
00:02:46,777 --> 00:02:48,161
Too slow.

69
00:02:49,796 --> 00:02:51,893
I have it figured out.

70
00:02:52,229 --> 00:02:54,158
Yes, I knew it.

71
00:02:56,381 --> 00:02:59,108
I've had to reinforce my footing
with cursed energy

72
00:02:59,317 --> 00:03:01,121
to avoid getting sucked in.

73
00:03:03,553 --> 00:03:04,854
[footsteps splashing]

74
00:03:05,986 --> 00:03:08,545
Because the whole bottom
of this domain

75
00:03:08,754 --> 00:03:10,432
is your shadow, right?

76
00:03:10,768 --> 00:03:13,788
You're able to remove
and store objects and yourself.

77
00:03:13,997 --> 00:03:15,466
That's pretty convenient.

78
00:03:15,759 --> 00:03:17,319
But one thing
kept nagging at me.

79
00:03:17,527 --> 00:03:19,911
"Why doesn't this guy have
more weapons he can use?"

80
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:23,090
You just use that one paltry
cursed tool over and over.

81
00:03:23,299 --> 00:03:24,847
Maybe it's a low-capacity tool

82
00:03:25,055 --> 00:03:27,356
and you're trying to reserve
as much space for yourself,

83
00:03:27,356 --> 00:03:29,530
just in case you need it
for something later on.

84
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:31,287
Either that,

85
00:03:31,287 --> 00:03:33,379
or you're being forced to bear
the weight of the objects

86
00:03:33,587 --> 00:03:35,135
that are stored in your shadow.

87
00:03:35,344 --> 00:03:36,933
[struggling]

88
00:03:37,937 --> 00:03:40,488
[REGGIE] Sounds like
the latter was spot-on.

89
00:03:40,697 --> 00:03:43,291
Now I've turned the design
of your domain against you.

90
00:03:43,834 --> 00:03:45,549
With three passenger cars,

91
00:03:45,549 --> 00:03:48,686
your current weight
is approximately 2.4 tons.

92
00:03:48,686 --> 00:03:51,697
Looks like your clones
weren't able to tolerate it.

93
00:03:51,697 --> 00:03:54,917
And I bet you can't even
produce your shikigami now.

94
00:03:55,587 --> 00:03:57,552
Either way, I'll just need
to keep minding

95
00:03:57,761 --> 00:03:58,849
my footing around you,

96
00:03:59,351 --> 00:04:01,191
as I keep adding weight

97
00:04:01,191 --> 00:04:03,617
until you're crushed under it.

98
00:04:06,042 --> 00:04:08,217
[MEGUMI]
Are you stupid or something?

99
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,007
Even if it's incomplete,

100
00:04:11,326 --> 00:04:12,840
a domain is still a domain!

101
00:04:13,404 --> 00:04:16,096
My shadow is everywhere!

102
00:04:22,827 --> 00:04:24,434
[trumpets]

103
00:04:26,389 --> 00:04:28,343
[groans]

104
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,639
Which one of us
will get crushed first?

105
00:04:31,848 --> 00:04:34,494
-Huh, Reggie?!
-[Reggie grunts]

106
00:04:34,915 --> 00:04:37,098
[♪ opening theme song playing]

107
00:05:09,231 --> 00:05:13,515
JUJUTSU KAISEN
THE CULLING GAME PART 1

108
00:06:05,054 --> 00:06:06,524
[whooshing]

109
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:11,019
[NARRATOR] It is said
that a typical human

110
00:06:11,228 --> 00:06:14,421
will lose consciousness
at five to six Gs.

111
00:06:15,009 --> 00:06:16,289
2.4 tons.

112
00:06:16,504 --> 00:06:19,382
Because Fushiguro
weighed only 60 kilograms,

113
00:06:19,382 --> 00:06:21,187
that meant he was
currently suffering

114
00:06:21,403 --> 00:06:24,110
the equivalent of 40 Gs.

115
00:06:24,969 --> 00:06:27,633
In order to prevent his blood
from pooling in his legs

116
00:06:27,633 --> 00:06:29,008
from the high Gs,

117
00:06:29,008 --> 00:06:31,200
and depriving his brain
of blood flow,

118
00:06:31,414 --> 00:06:33,606
Fushiguro was lowering
his posture,

119
00:06:33,820 --> 00:06:36,399
and reinforcing his body
with cursed energy,

120
00:06:36,614 --> 00:06:39,020
paying special attention
to his legs.

121
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:45,250
A mature African elephant
weighs three to six tons.

122
00:06:46,265 --> 00:06:49,480
With the domain's improvement
to his technique's accuracy,

123
00:06:49,691 --> 00:06:53,371
Max Elephant accurately
recreated its real weight.

124
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:54,978
Under that weight,

125
00:06:54,978 --> 00:06:58,743
Reggie Star's right fibula
and heel bone were cracking.

126
00:06:58,955 --> 00:07:00,477
[Reggie groans]

127
00:07:00,688 --> 00:07:03,269
[NARRATOR] Both of them
were now under enormous strain,

128
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:06,018
and faced the possibility
of being crushed to death

129
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:07,030
at any second.

130
00:07:07,119 --> 00:07:08,515
[both struggling]

131
00:07:08,853 --> 00:07:10,545
[REGGIE] I screwed up.

132
00:07:10,756 --> 00:07:13,717
I could've won if I had kept
the trucks in reserve.

133
00:07:13,929 --> 00:07:14,929
What do I do?

134
00:07:14,929 --> 00:07:17,370
I got splashed with some water
at the same time,

135
00:07:17,592 --> 00:07:19,322
but my trump card's
still safe.

136
00:07:19,945 --> 00:07:21,631
I could slip into his shadow

137
00:07:21,852 --> 00:07:24,205
and recreate my trump card
inside it.

138
00:07:24,205 --> 00:07:26,203
That would crush him for sure.

139
00:07:28,466 --> 00:07:31,839
No, he's not dismissing
his domain.

140
00:07:32,061 --> 00:07:33,925
But when he does decide
to dismiss it,

141
00:07:33,925 --> 00:07:35,612
that means
anything still in his shadow

142
00:07:35,612 --> 00:07:37,742
is going to be stuck
inside there.

143
00:07:37,964 --> 00:07:40,050
What if I'm stuck
in his shadow forever?

144
00:07:40,493 --> 00:07:42,535
I'll be there
even after he dies!

145
00:07:42,757 --> 00:07:45,199
What's it like
inside his shadow, anyway?

146
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:46,199
It looks like a liquid,

147
00:07:46,403 --> 00:07:48,032
but what if I can't
breathe in it?

148
00:07:48,236 --> 00:07:49,254
Can I float?

149
00:07:49,458 --> 00:07:50,720
Keep fighting!

150
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,431
Submerging into his shadow
is too risky.

151
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,224
Ah, I'm out of time.

152
00:07:54,428 --> 00:07:56,464
So while stuck in this state,

153
00:07:56,669 --> 00:07:59,153
I have to pull out my trump card

154
00:07:59,357 --> 00:08:00,702
and activate it!

155
00:08:01,516 --> 00:08:02,779
[grunts]

156
00:08:03,105 --> 00:08:04,164
[gasps]

157
00:08:04,857 --> 00:08:07,708
Contractual Re-Creation!

158
00:08:07,993 --> 00:08:10,193
SNAP

159
00:08:10,397 --> 00:08:14,267
[Megumi struggling]

160
00:08:14,471 --> 00:08:15,896
[straining]

161
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:28,540
[REGGIE]
I didn't make it in time.

162
00:08:28,751 --> 00:08:31,794
And now I know there's no oxygen
inside of his shadow.

163
00:08:32,766 --> 00:08:34,246
No buoyancy

164
00:08:34,457 --> 00:08:36,064
or resistance, either.

165
00:08:38,305 --> 00:08:39,615
I'm just...

166
00:08:41,263 --> 00:08:42,701
sinking.

167
00:08:44,012 --> 00:08:45,618
My consciousness...

168
00:08:46,336 --> 00:08:48,577
is fading.

169
00:08:51,705 --> 00:08:54,157
[Megumi groans] Not yet.

170
00:08:54,368 --> 00:08:55,510
Keep enduring it.

171
00:08:55,890 --> 00:08:57,793
Gotta wait until
I'm sure he's dead

172
00:08:57,793 --> 00:08:59,738
before dismissing the domain!

173
00:08:59,949 --> 00:09:02,316
Then I can expel
whatever's in my shadow.

174
00:09:02,528 --> 00:09:05,571
[straining]

175
00:09:28,991 --> 00:09:31,020
[gasps, coughs]

176
00:09:31,231 --> 00:09:33,218
[coughing]

177
00:09:35,078 --> 00:09:37,107
[REGGIE] The things I recreate,

178
00:09:37,784 --> 00:09:39,601
they disappear
soon after carrying out

179
00:09:39,813 --> 00:09:42,011
whatever command
I gave them to carry out.

180
00:09:42,011 --> 00:09:45,140
However, I didn't give
those cars I sank any commands.

181
00:09:45,351 --> 00:09:48,352
After all, I didn't want them
disappearing on me.

182
00:09:48,859 --> 00:09:51,565
That means I could still issue
them a command if I want.

183
00:09:51,776 --> 00:09:53,890
Something like
"Take me and rise up."

184
00:09:54,398 --> 00:09:56,004
The weight
of one car is gone now,

185
00:09:56,215 --> 00:09:58,963
but it was totally worth it
to save my life.

186
00:09:59,174 --> 00:10:00,780
[Megumi straining]

187
00:10:03,148 --> 00:10:04,627
[REGGIE] Tell you what!

188
00:10:04,838 --> 00:10:07,333
I am man enough to admit it!

189
00:10:07,544 --> 00:10:08,813
You are strong.

190
00:10:09,911 --> 00:10:12,026
But not as strong as me!

191
00:10:13,251 --> 00:10:16,084
Contractual Re-Creation!

192
00:10:16,295 --> 00:10:18,494
[♪ tense music playing]

193
00:10:21,622 --> 00:10:27,075
A 132-square-foot, two-story
wooden frame structure!

194
00:10:27,075 --> 00:10:30,034
The framework alone weighs
at least 30 tons!

195
00:10:30,456 --> 00:10:33,035
And I'm commanding it
to crush you!

196
00:10:33,246 --> 00:10:35,614
[screams]

197
00:10:57,174 --> 00:10:59,541
[Megumi straining]

198
00:11:00,175 --> 00:11:01,486
[music ends]

199
00:11:05,629 --> 00:11:07,090
[Reggie gasps] What happened?

200
00:11:07,577 --> 00:11:09,429
Did I fall back
into his shadow again?

201
00:11:11,429 --> 00:11:13,615
No! I'm in actual water.

202
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:14,798
How?

203
00:11:15,441 --> 00:11:17,005
It's heavy.

204
00:11:17,005 --> 00:11:19,887
What's the brat trying to do,
strangle me?

205
00:11:20,669 --> 00:11:21,669
What power!

206
00:11:22,529 --> 00:11:23,988
No. That's wrong.

207
00:11:23,988 --> 00:11:26,709
This is from the weight
of those two cars that I added.

208
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:30,909
This is bad.

209
00:11:31,047 --> 00:11:32,679
This time, I'm really sinking!

210
00:11:33,311 --> 00:11:36,594
I have to dismiss
Contractual Re-Creation!

211
00:11:51,186 --> 00:11:52,966
[gasps]

212
00:11:53,163 --> 00:11:55,773
[panting]

213
00:11:55,971 --> 00:11:57,078
All right.

214
00:11:57,276 --> 00:11:58,779
The community gymnasium.

215
00:11:58,977 --> 00:12:01,705
And in the gym's basement
is a heated swimming pool.

216
00:12:04,078 --> 00:12:07,163
Did he go hiding in a shadow
and dismiss his domain?

217
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,021
That could' ve forced me
to destroy the floor

218
00:12:09,220 --> 00:12:10,379
and plunge into the pool.

219
00:12:10,589 --> 00:12:11,899
[grunts]

220
00:12:13,124 --> 00:12:14,519
[MEGUMI]
You can't use your receipts

221
00:12:14,730 --> 00:12:17,687
when they're that wet, can you?

222
00:12:20,814 --> 00:12:23,856
[REGGIE] He waited instead of
pursuing me right away.

223
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:26,179
Does that mean his technique
still needs to recover

224
00:12:26,391 --> 00:12:27,573
after his domain exhausted it?

225
00:12:28,461 --> 00:12:29,981
That's what you think?

226
00:12:30,193 --> 00:12:31,502
Are you sure?

227
00:12:32,348 --> 00:12:34,671
I'm sure that you can't
produce your shikigami

228
00:12:34,883 --> 00:12:36,150
in your current condition.

229
00:12:37,502 --> 00:12:38,854
[MEGUMI] Yeah, that's true.

230
00:12:38,854 --> 00:12:42,149
So you do understand
what comes next, don't ya?

231
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:46,754
[REGGIE] He's going to use
a shikigami, just not that dog.

232
00:12:46,965 --> 00:12:49,585
But none of his other ones
can deal a decisive blow.

233
00:12:49,796 --> 00:12:51,360
Fine. Use it!

234
00:12:51,571 --> 00:12:53,092
The moment
that you let up on me,

235
00:12:53,303 --> 00:12:55,077
I'll finish you
with a counterattack!

236
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:30,144
[both grunting]

237
00:13:46,198 --> 00:13:49,156
You thought Demon Dog
was some weak shikigami?

238
00:13:49,704 --> 00:13:51,015
You were wrong.

239
00:13:52,028 --> 00:13:53,719
What did I tell you before?

240
00:13:53,930 --> 00:13:55,958
We sorcerers are all liars.

241
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:57,168
-[groans]
-[thuds]

242
00:13:58,112 --> 00:14:00,098
JUJUTSU KAISEN

243
00:14:03,225 --> 00:14:04,914
JUJUTSU KAISEN

244
00:14:04,914 --> 00:14:07,829
[♪ tranquil music playing,
Camille Saint-Saëns "Le Cygne"]

245
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:15,139
[REGGIE] The domain.

246
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:16,490
The pool.

247
00:14:16,913 --> 00:14:18,181
All to convince me

248
00:14:18,392 --> 00:14:20,589
you couldn't use
that dog anymore.

249
00:14:21,096 --> 00:14:24,011
You didn't escape
into this gymnasium.

250
00:14:24,222 --> 00:14:25,785
You lured me into it.

251
00:14:26,884 --> 00:14:29,883
To think I'd let
a modern sorcerer,

252
00:14:30,095 --> 00:14:33,010
and a brat at that,
get the better of me.

253
00:14:35,122 --> 00:14:37,192
Nue can't fly that far
carrying me,

254
00:14:37,403 --> 00:14:38,544
so I couldn't escape.

255
00:14:39,009 --> 00:14:40,329
I've had trouble
with that before.

256
00:14:46,153 --> 00:14:47,301
Tell me,

257
00:14:47,513 --> 00:14:49,384
how are you connected
to Tengen?

258
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:55,889
Who are you talking about?

259
00:14:56,568 --> 00:14:59,502
Oh, right, Tengen.

260
00:14:59,715 --> 00:15:01,968
That hermit
would still be alive.

261
00:15:02,691 --> 00:15:05,200
Must be history's
greatest shut-in.

262
00:15:05,412 --> 00:15:07,070
Okay. That's enough.

263
00:15:09,111 --> 00:15:10,598
Reggie said Tengen's claims

264
00:15:10,812 --> 00:15:12,852
about the Culling Game
were a bluff.

265
00:15:14,128 --> 00:15:16,253
I'd be smart
to consider the possibility

266
00:15:16,465 --> 00:15:19,144
Tengen and Kenjaku
are secretly connected,

267
00:15:19,357 --> 00:15:21,695
and that they're both lying
about their endgames.

268
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:25,479
But that doesn't seem likely
from Reggie's reaction.

269
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:30,028
Kogane,

270
00:15:30,326 --> 00:15:34,407
transfer all my points over
to this little brat.

271
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:35,620
[KOGANE] Okay.

272
00:15:36,993 --> 00:15:38,284
Congratulations,

273
00:15:38,491 --> 00:15:41,363
you have been granted 41 points
by Reggie Star.

274
00:15:41,572 --> 00:15:42,862
And in return?

275
00:15:43,445 --> 00:15:46,150
Must you assume
I have some evil plot?

276
00:15:46,358 --> 00:15:49,396
I want to do at least
one good deed before I die.

277
00:15:50,021 --> 00:15:52,601
By the way,
I'm just a spectator here.

278
00:15:52,810 --> 00:15:55,806
Kenjaku and I weren't
ever close friends.

279
00:15:56,014 --> 00:15:57,305
But I do like this game.

280
00:15:57,512 --> 00:15:59,385
It certainly
makes things interesting.

281
00:15:59,968 --> 00:16:02,174
That's my intuition anyway.

282
00:16:03,464 --> 00:16:05,462
Now do me a favor.

283
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:07,834
After all, you did kill me.

284
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:10,331
The favor is,

285
00:16:10,748 --> 00:16:12,496
let fate toy with you

286
00:16:12,995 --> 00:16:15,243
before you die like a fool.

287
00:16:15,451 --> 00:16:18,364
♪

288
00:16:38,425 --> 00:16:41,006
[KOGANE] You have gained
five points for a kill.

289
00:16:43,087 --> 00:16:44,918
[whooshing]

290
00:16:45,751 --> 00:16:47,125
[sips, grunts]

291
00:16:53,992 --> 00:16:55,199
I got him!

292
00:16:55,781 --> 00:16:57,863
Nope! 'Cause you
dropped your guard!

293
00:16:59,069 --> 00:17:00,651
You think you're Mr. Tough Guy?

294
00:17:00,860 --> 00:17:01,860
What the hell!

295
00:17:01,860 --> 00:17:04,771
Ugh! Why is your whole body
covered in lotion?

296
00:17:05,007 --> 00:17:06,697
It might actually be sauce.

297
00:17:06,932 --> 00:17:08,482
Just die!

298
00:17:09,093 --> 00:17:10,784
[groans]

299
00:17:11,018 --> 00:17:12,897
I pray it's only sauce!

300
00:17:13,413 --> 00:17:15,620
Seriously, what's with this guy?

301
00:17:15,856 --> 00:17:17,500
I've blown him up a lot!

302
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:18,519
I feel like I've killed him
at least five times.

303
00:17:18,733 --> 00:17:21,428
So how come he has
so little damage?

304
00:17:21,642 --> 00:17:23,097
SO LITTLE.

305
00:17:23,311 --> 00:17:24,766
What's wrong with sauce?

306
00:17:25,022 --> 00:17:27,631
[IORI] Even his giant
head wound has healed up.

307
00:17:28,273 --> 00:17:29,728
But he hasn't shown any signs

308
00:17:29,942 --> 00:17:31,739
of using
reverse cursed techniques

309
00:17:31,953 --> 00:17:33,237
like I do.

310
00:17:33,450 --> 00:17:35,419
I don't get
what's going on with him.

311
00:17:35,761 --> 00:17:37,258
Player Hazenoki.

312
00:17:37,472 --> 00:17:38,472
What'd you want?

313
00:17:38,670 --> 00:17:39,825
I regret to inform you

314
00:17:40,039 --> 00:17:41,965
that player Reggie Star
has just died.

315
00:17:42,178 --> 00:17:43,178
Huh?

316
00:17:45,729 --> 00:17:47,227
[exclaims] Where you goin'?

317
00:17:47,441 --> 00:17:48,681
[IORI] I'm goin' home.

318
00:17:48,896 --> 00:17:49,964
I'm sick of this.

319
00:17:50,179 --> 00:17:51,976
[TAKABA] Oh. Well, take a bath!

320
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:53,190
And brush your teeth!

321
00:17:54,461 --> 00:17:55,534
[gasps]

322
00:17:56,049 --> 00:17:58,790
Hey! How about
giving me your points?

323
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:00,389
Don't follow me.

324
00:18:00,598 --> 00:18:01,730
Oh, come on!

325
00:18:01,730 --> 00:18:03,995
Just think of it
as paying it forward.

326
00:18:04,205 --> 00:18:05,630
Just die.

327
00:18:05,630 --> 00:18:07,769
[NARRATOR] Takaba's
cursed technique, Comedian,

328
00:18:07,979 --> 00:18:10,201
takes whatever he's convinced
would be funny,

329
00:18:10,411 --> 00:18:12,172
and turns it into a reality.

330
00:18:12,382 --> 00:18:16,157
Even Satoru Gojo is incapable
of opposing this technique.

331
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:22,991
Yet Takaba is utterly clueless
as to how his technique works.

332
00:18:23,831 --> 00:18:26,640
[Remi panting]

333
00:18:31,757 --> 00:18:33,811
[REMI]
I don't get it, I don't get it!

334
00:18:34,021 --> 00:18:37,124
Ever since I became an adult,
I hardly understand anything.

335
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:40,101
[panting]

336
00:18:42,869 --> 00:18:45,637
I've heard that all men
are actually wolves.

337
00:18:45,847 --> 00:18:47,189
But it's always those wolves

338
00:18:47,189 --> 00:18:49,202
who take care of
the confusing stuff for me.

339
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:55,912
It's a win-win situation.

340
00:18:56,121 --> 00:18:57,547
The wolves love being in charge,

341
00:18:57,756 --> 00:18:59,853
and I love not thinking
about anything.

342
00:19:00,063 --> 00:19:02,915
Men always want to do stuff
for me because I'm so cute.

343
00:19:06,857 --> 00:19:09,625
[panting]

344
00:19:09,834 --> 00:19:12,937
The wolves
will always, always--

345
00:19:13,147 --> 00:19:15,495
-[snarls]
-[gasps]

346
00:19:21,743 --> 00:19:24,092
[TSUMIKI] Megumi, don't.

347
00:19:30,927 --> 00:19:32,396
[REMI] You're not killing me?

348
00:19:33,025 --> 00:19:34,366
[footsteps receding]

349
00:19:40,573 --> 00:19:42,334
[MEGUMI] Damn it, sis.

350
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:44,514
[thuds]

351
00:19:45,731 --> 00:19:47,576
Shut up already.

352
00:19:55,208 --> 00:19:57,683
[♪ ethereal music playing]

353
00:20:07,622 --> 00:20:10,515
[NARRATOR] Events progressed
quickly in the Sendai Colony,

354
00:20:10,725 --> 00:20:12,318
far outstripping those of Tokyo.

355
00:20:12,695 --> 00:20:16,008
They also started
to become increasingly fierce.

356
00:20:17,938 --> 00:20:19,615
Dhruv Lakdawalla.

357
00:20:19,825 --> 00:20:22,131
Current points, 91.

358
00:20:22,341 --> 00:20:24,563
This is his second incarnation.

359
00:20:25,402 --> 00:20:27,751
He's an old man
who single-handedly

360
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:31,440
conquered this archipelago
during the Civil War of Wa.

361
00:20:31,651 --> 00:20:34,208
He possesses
two autonomous shikigami,

362
00:20:34,419 --> 00:20:38,193
and the orbit of those shikigami
determines his domain.

363
00:20:41,128 --> 00:20:42,763
Ryu Ishigori.

364
00:20:42,973 --> 00:20:45,153
Current points, 77.

365
00:20:45,951 --> 00:20:48,299
He has the greatest
cursed energy firepower

366
00:20:48,509 --> 00:20:50,815
among any other remaining
player in the game.

367
00:20:52,492 --> 00:20:54,044
Takako Uro.

368
00:20:54,254 --> 00:20:56,057
Current points, 70.

369
00:20:56,267 --> 00:20:57,819
She was originally the captain

370
00:20:58,028 --> 00:21:00,293
of the Sun, Moon,
and Stars Squad.

371
00:21:00,502 --> 00:21:02,515
Assassins for the Fujiwara Clan.

372
00:21:02,934 --> 00:21:06,037
Her technique can
manipulate the sky.

373
00:21:07,464 --> 00:21:08,764
Kurourushi.

374
00:21:08,973 --> 00:21:10,944
Current points, 54.

375
00:21:11,364 --> 00:21:14,551
A cockroach cursed spirit
that Kenjaku freed

376
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:17,612
from the control
of cursed spirit manipulation.

377
00:21:17,948 --> 00:21:21,512
It ranks as a previously
registered special-grade.

378
00:21:22,854 --> 00:21:24,531
It's currently lying dormant

379
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:26,712
until certain conditions
are met.

380
00:21:28,054 --> 00:21:30,235
There was no alliance
between them,

381
00:21:30,444 --> 00:21:33,506
but their complex compatibility
and opposing strength

382
00:21:33,715 --> 00:21:36,316
led them into
a four-way stalemate.

383
00:21:36,734 --> 00:21:39,209
But one of those pillars...

384
00:21:39,418 --> 00:21:40,467
[slashes]

385
00:21:40,845 --> 00:21:42,060
...has fallen.

386
00:21:43,319 --> 00:21:44,319
Yuta Okkotsu.

387
00:21:44,465 --> 00:21:46,112
Current points, 35.

388
00:21:46,259 --> 00:21:47,465
Three months
after the Night Parade

389
00:21:47,465 --> 00:21:48,465
of a Hundred Demons,

390
00:21:48,523 --> 00:21:50,376
he blossomed
as a special-grade sorcerer.

391
00:21:50,523 --> 00:21:51,699
He is a modern sorcerer,

392
00:21:51,846 --> 00:21:52,993
rivaling the abilities
of even...

393
00:21:53,199 --> 00:21:54,399
Satoru Gojo.

394
00:21:55,766 --> 00:21:58,060
[♪ closing theme song playing]

395
00:23:31,839 --> 00:23:33,500
[YUTA] I'll obtain
400 points on my own.

396
00:23:33,651 --> 00:23:34,922
[RIKA] Which would
you like, Yuta?

397
00:23:35,073 --> 00:23:36,193
[KOGANE]
It's called Kurourushi!

398
00:23:36,193 --> 00:23:38,189
-[YUTA] I'll take it all!
-[RIKA] Give me back Yuta!

399
00:23:38,340 --> 00:23:40,488
[YUTA] I refuse to let you
kill your best friend twice.

400
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:41,911
NEXT EPISODE
SENDAI COLONY
